        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 7 at 4:10AM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 409 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 8 miles northeast of San Rafael Ranch Airport, or 11
miles east of Agua Nueva, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Puesta Del Sol Airport and Agua Nueva.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
Deep South Texas.</instruction>
